  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\nBUG REPORT\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nStatefulSet Status is missing `updatedReplicas` field but has `updateRevision` set\r\n```\r\nstatus:\r\n  currentReplicas: 1\r\n  currentRevision: consul-example-703895715\r\n  observedGeneration: 1\r\n  readyReplicas: 1\r\n  replicas: 1\r\n  updateRevision: consul-example-703895715\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nAccording to the docs in https://kubernetes.io/docs/api-reference/v1.7/#statefulsetstatus-v1beta1-apps:\r\n> updatedReplicas is the number of Pods created by the StatefulSet controller from the StatefulSet version indicated by updateRevision.\r\n\r\n It seems that `updatedReplicas` is actually only useful when doing a rolling update, if that is the case we should unset `updateRevision` to avoid confusion here. Otherwise, for a statefulset that is updated and not doing a rolling update, `updatedReplicas` should equal `currentReplicas`. \r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nCreate a statefulset on v1.7.3\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): v1.7.3\r\n\r\n/sig apps\r\n",
